Prince William in Afghanistan
2010-11-15 08:10:53 GMT
prince William joined British Defence Secretary Liam Fox to commemorate Remembrance Day with British troops, during a surprise visit to Afghanistan at the weekend.The prince placed a wreath at a plaque listing fallen soldiers of both World Wars and later conflicts, which included the names of some of his friends.Two minutes of silence was followed by prayers.The U.K. royal later met with troops based at Camp Bastion in Helmand province, on what was his second trip to the country.There have been more than 340 British military deaths since Britain joined the war in Afghanistan in 2001.Kirsty Basset, Reuters.

